text: Zosia Russell MametAccording to Vermont Births, 1981–2001, and Vermont Birth Records, 1909–2008, at Ancestry.com. (; born February 2, 1988) is an American actress and musician. Her best known television roles were in Mad Men, United States of Tara and Parenthood and as Shoshanna Shapiro on the HBO original series Girls. ==References== Category:1988 births Category:American television actors Category:Living people Category:American stage actors Category:American movie actors Category:American voice actors Category:Actors from Vermont Category:Musicians from Vermont
